Adding experimental git-remote-link tool.

This tool takes in a filename plus an optional line in your local repo and outputs a link to github for that file/line.

Merge pull request #55 from avih/mozillabuild-fixes

Mozillabuild fixes

handle missing python2 gracefully

If python2 is missing, git-push-to-hg will fail after already modified the
mercurial repo state. So abort gracefully before starting on such case.

Scripts which are python(2) themselves will fail before starting. Currently
git-push-to-hg is the only bash script which invokes a python(2) script.

Also add a note at the README about handling it with Windows mozilla-build.
msys: only apply path normalization if we need them

Merge pull request #37 from walac/master

Fix suppression of "PATCH" prefix in subject line.

Fix suppression of "PATCH" prefix in subject line.

If more than one patch are generated by "git format-patch", the subject
lines will start with the pattern "[PATCH N/M] " instead of "[PATCH] ".
This causes the converted patch include the PATCH prefix.

We fix this by using a regular expression to match either "[PATCH] " or
"[PATCH N/M] " prefixes.

"[PATH N/M]" patter occurs when you format-patch more than one commit at
once.

Restore previous patch queue after git-push-to-trychooser

Explicitly use Python 2 in the shebang

Some systems, notably Arch Linux, have decided that because they're
bleeding edge, they're going to have /usr/bin/python set to Python 3
instead of Python 2. Of course, this wreaks havoc with applications that
are (reasonably) expecting /usr/bin/python to be Python 2, but what can
you do?

Therefore, explicitly request `python2` instead of `python` in the
shebang line.

Merge pull request #38 from amccreight/FixTracks

Fix tracks

Restore some additional behavior for git-tracks with other combinations of arguments.

With no arguments at all, git-tracks should use HEAD, while treating a lack of upstream as an error.

With -d, git-tracks should see if there is another argument, and use it as the branch.

Restore the behavior of |git tracks -d| for branches with no upstream set.

Fixes #36.
